\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ son of Azzur. He was his grandson, and for the following reason Scripture traced his lineage, [viz.] to 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ teach that whoever flatters a wicked man eventually falls into his hands or into the hands of his son or 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ into the hands of his grandson, and Jeremiah flattered him, for he said to him, “Amen! (28:6) [So may 
